title: Volleyball roundup: Lady Cats drop home finale
text:
Volleyball roundup: Lady Cats drop home finale Herald Democrat 
Fresh off a thrilling five-set comeback win against Denison on Friday, Sherman gave first-place Prosper a battle in the opening set before falling, 25-20, 25-9, 25-10, on Tuesday night in District 10-5A play at Bearcat Gymnasium. 
Dallas Aleman had 16 assists and Paige Aleman added 13 digs in the Lady Cats’ final home match of the season. Rylie Bernard had five kills and Sarah Graham finished with three kills and four blocks. 
The Lady Cats (13-23, 2-10) travel to Wylie High on Friday and close out the season next Tuesday at Lovejoy. 
District 12-4A Melissa def. Princeton 3-2 
MELISSA — Alli Boedeker had 15 kills as Melissa outlasted Princeton, 21-25, 25-14, 25-21, 22-25, 16-14, to clinch a playoff spot and move into a tie for first place on Tuesday night. 
Haley Bazis added 12 kills, Riley Duzenack totaled 11 kills, 38 assists, six aces and 10 digs, Kim Ortleb collected 17 digs and Amanda Kocsis finished with 14 digs for Melissa (20-13, 6-2), which plays at Community on Friday. 
District 10-3A Gunter def. S&S 3-0 
SADLER — Mikayla Watson had 15 kills, seven assists, six digs and five aces as first-place Gunter defeated S&S, 25-11, 25-14, 25-7, in district action on Tuesday night. 
Katey Campbell added nine kills, eight assists and five aces, Camryn MacDonald chipped in five kills and five aces and Kaycie Hamilton totaled 10 digs for Gunter (29-2, 12-0), which hosts second-place Callisburg on Friday. 
Whitesboro def. Ponder 3-1 
WHITESBORO — Delani Dickson had 16 kills and four digs as Whitesboro kept its playoff hopes alive with a 25-16, 22-25, 25-18, 25-21 victory against Ponder in district play on Tuesday night. 
The win moved Whitesboro (22-15, 6-6) just a game behind Ponder (14-13, 7-5) with two matches remaining and the Lady Bearcats hold the tie-breaker. Whitesboro plays at Pilot Point on Friday while Ponder visits Pottsboro. 
Phoenix West added 12 kills and eight digs, Lauren Purdom chipped in nine kills and six blocks, Taylor Brown and Karlee Schuessler each put down four kills, Jess Abney handed out 20 assists to go with nine digs, Casey Lang finished with 21 assists and seven digs and Molly Miller collected 18 digs for Whitesboro. 
Pottsboro def. Howe 3-0 
HOWE — Madeline O’Hanlon had 10 kills, five digs and three aces as Pottsboro defeated Howe, 25-7, 25-18, 25-8, to clinch a playoff spot in district action on Tuesday night. 
Destiny Daniel added 10 kills and five aces, Rani Elder chipped in six kills, Hatty Shope and Kelli Frye each handed out 16 assists and Ansleigh Oakley collected 10 digs for third-place Pottsboro (28-10, 9-3), which hosts fourth-place Ponder on Friday. 
District 13-3A Farmersville def. Whitewright 3-0 
FARMERSVILLE — Jamie Kelly had seven kills and 10 digs for Whitewright but first-place Farmersville defeated the Lady Tigers, 25-14, 25-11, 25-7, in district action on Tuesday. 
Caroline Rahm added four kills, Daley Wylie chipped in three kills and Jolie Donaldson collected six digs for Whitewright (11-23, 1-11). 
Commerce def. Tom Bean 3-0 
TOM BEAN — Haley Ford had five kills and seven blocks for Tom Bean but Commerce defeated the Lady Tomcats, 26-24, 25-10, 25-11, in district play on Tuesday. 
Baylee Stautzenberger put down kills, Ramie Byers added five assists and five digs, Jillian Beck handed out 11 assists and Isabel Tormos collected seven digs for Tom Bean. 
District 11-2A Bells def. Dodd City 3-0 
BELLS — Catie Beall had 11 kills and 11 assists as Bells defeated Dodd City, 26-24, 25-18, 25-22, in district action on Tuesday night. 
Zoe Bankston added eight kills, Cheyenne McMillen chipped in six kills and four blocks and Bailey Wornhor totaled three kills and two digs for first-place Bells. 
Lindsay Carter had 15 kills, Fallon Hilliard added nine kills, Abby Weeks handed out 22 assists and Sarah Brent and Madelyn Underwood collected three digs apiece for Dodd City.
